The NATO-certified Beretta Px4 Storm Inox double/single-action semiauto is the culmination Beretta’s experience in engineering pistols for military and law enforcement. Super-Durable and Safe

Designed to meet the most stringent military standards of durability, the PX4 has been reported to fire well over 150,000 rounds with zero part breakages. Besides the essential simplicity of its design (fewer parts=fewer and more solid components bearing stress), the proprietary steel we use for this pistol was developed to be impossibly tough. Its safety system is also ultra-reliable, giving you automatic firing pin block as well as a flip-up ambidextous manual safety for extra peace of mind. Soft-Shooting, Strong and Easy to Maintain

This pistol features a cold-hammer forged, rotary barrel encased in an ultra-tough slide machined out of solid bar stock. Besides being one of the strongest actions available, the rotary barrel dissipates recoil away from the shooter’s hand and greatly reduces muzzle jump, making it an extremely fast, accurate and pleasant-shooting handgun. After a long day at the range, the disassembly device is designed to allow the pistol to be field stripped very quickly and easily and to avoid casual or involuntary disassembly. Re-assembly is even easier, with the slide locking automatically when it travels past the rear section of the frame.
Perfect for Concealed Carry and Loaded with Features

The lines of the pistol are snag-free and make unholstering and reholstering easy and fluid, while the trigger guard is also rounded to facilitate the correct position of the supporting hand. In front of the trigger guard there is a Picatinny rail integral to the frame, allowing the easy mounting of laser devices, light systems or other types of accessories. The pistol may be adapted to different hand sizes and shooting styles thanks to a modular design with interchangeable backstraps. Also, the ambidextrous and reversible controls offer the possibility of easily training or shooting with either hand.

title: For Sale:  M1A Supermatch w/Accessories- Amazing Rifle
location: upper bucks county, Southeastern, PA, Pennsylvania
postcontent: This is a top of the line SUPERMATCH version of the ultra reliable and supremely accurate M1A. This rifle is in excellent shape, with no scratches or damaging marks. It has the oversize walnut stock and is factory glass bedded.  It is a "pre-ban" with the lugged flash suppressor.    It has a 2 stage match trigger which has a "soft stop" just at the spot which engages the firing pin.  The sights are national match iron sights w/covers.  i used to successfully shoot targets at 1000yds with these.  It comes with the matching bayonette (US M8A1) that attaches to said lugged flash suppressor.  It also has many mags (five  20 rds and one 5 rd).  It also comes with ~2/3 of a case of military ammo (non-corrosive) and 2 boxes of match grade ammo.  The photos cannot do it justice.  It is amazing to shoot, like a precision machine.  It puts the modern AR- rifles to shame when I'm at the range.  People are always commenting and admiring it.  I have not been using it for the past few years (got family, no time to shoot) and so it is time to sell it.  It lives in a silicone sock (water repelling) in my humidity controlled safe, so no oxidation anywhere.  Really pristine, an amazing piece of history.  Very similar to the M14 sniper rifle developed from the M1 Garand, and used by the miliarty from the Vietnam War onward to today.  Ships via my FFL to your FFL.  If its not legal in your state, then please don't try to buy it.  Please email for more photos or phone/text contact info.  For more info see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M1A_rifle and check the listing for serial number 045680. Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  "idiots" beware!
postcontent:
Professionals are everywhere! They are lurking in every isle and corner of the gun store and gun show, waiting to prey on you, the unsuspecting "idiot". Please remember that these "professionals" live, eat, and breathe gun. They are fairly easy to spot, they are usually "blue in the face" from blah-blah-blahing about guns. Then, when they are finished victimizing YOU the "idiots", they sit on their couches with a shotgun news in one hand and favorite gun in the other and watch back- to- back Walking Dead.
The main thing to remember when dealing guns with  "professionals" is that "they" WILL NOT take a loss on a deal. They will "screw" you out of your stuff, then pass the "screwing" on to another "idiot".     
         I call out to all gun "idiots", keep fighting the good fight. Keep the "professionals" in-check. Help your fellow brothers-in-arms, educating them on gun safety, maintenance/lubrication and gun values. Be proud, that it is the "idiots" money that keep the gunshows (professionals) in business. And lastly, forgive the professionals greedy hearts this holiday season.
